From 1bf5488799a0cef2d7dc6b14c7ccfbb24cb2c6f7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joshua-Eisenhart <40147598+Joshua-Eisenhart@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 13:51:13 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 27/35] test(claim-gate): tighten host-witness consume
 semantics; isolate redteam ledger roots

Adapter-bridge cases now assert the hardened boundary: a pass/pass
projection without host-executed witness gates is host_blocked, a
fail verdict is host_reviewed_failed (liveLevConsumed false in both).
Redteam temp roots get real Lev markers and use LEV_PROJECT_ROOT so
persisted host-trust ledgers isolate to the temp dir instead of
polluting the repo root (A22b/A22c isolation fix).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../proof/claim-gate-adapter-bridge.test.ts   | 34 +++++++++++++++----
 .../proof/claim-gate-redteam-targets.test.ts  | 24 ++++++++-----
 2 files changed, 43 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)

diff --git a/core/orchestration/src/proof/claim-gate-adapter-bridge.test.ts b/core/orchestration/src/proof/claim-gate-adapter-bridge.test.ts
index b082320cd..52c02c761 100644
